374T00000X	374T00000X	Nursing Service Related Providers	Religious Nonmedical Nursing Personnel	\N	Religious nonmedical nursing personnel are experienced in caring for the physical needs of nonmedical patients.  For example, caring for the physical needs such as assistance with activities of daily living; assistance with moving, positioning, and ambulation; nutritional needs; and comfort and support measures.	Source:  Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services [7/1/2009: title modified, definition modified]  Additional Resources: www.cms.hhs.gov/CertificationandComplianc/19_RNHCIs.asp   2005 Code of Federal Regulations, Title 42, Chapter IV, Part 403, Subpart G, 403.702 Definitions and Terms	\N	\N	\N	metaTaxonomyCode:374T00000X	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f
